
[1]smallness

   SMALL'NESS, n. Littleness of size or extent; littleness of quantity; as
   the smallness of a fly or of a horse; the smallness of a hill.

   2. Littleness in degree; as the smallness of trouble or pain.

   3. Littleness in force or strength; weakness; as smallness of mind or
   intellectual powers.

   4. Fineness; softness; melodiousness; as the smallness of a female
   voice.

   5. Littleness in amount of value; as the smallness of a sum.

   6. Littleness of importance; inconsideratbleness; as the smallness of
   an affair.
